  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The intended use is limited to pre-market design verification of impeller geometry variants operating in the flow range 2–6 L/min at 1500–3500 RPM. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-cpb-class2-worst-case",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis-benchmark",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/cpb-operating-conditions-envelope"
  ],
